LOEB v. TRUSTEES OF COLUMBIA TP., HAMILTON COUNTY. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. May 14, 1902.) No. 738. In Error to the Circuit Court of the United States for the Southern District of Ohio. C. Hammond Avery, H. D. Peck, and John W. Warrington, for plaintiff in error. Louis A. Ireton and Burch & Johnson, for defendant in error.

Before LUR-TON, DAY, and SEVERENS, Circuit Judges.

No opinion. Dismissed on stipulation of counsel.
